summary: The Cincinnati Bengals defeated the Dallas Cowboys 27-20 in an exciting Monday Night Football matchup. The game featured a back-and-forth battle throughout, with the Bengals ultimately securing the victory on a late touchdown by wide receiver Ja'Marr Chase. The Bengals' special teams unit also played a crucial role, contributing two field goals and a blocked punt that led to a touchdown. Despite a strong performance from Cowboys quarterback Dak Prescott, who threw for 278 yards and two touchdowns, the Bengals' defense managed to force a key turnover late in the game. The win puts the Bengals in a strong position to make the playoffs, while the Cowboys' playoff hopes suffered a setback.

name: Daniel Penny verdict
summary: In the highly publicized case of Daniel Penny, the former Marine charged in the subway chokehold death of Jordan Neely, a jury has found him not guilty of criminally negligent homicide. The manslaughter charge was previously dismissed during the trial. The verdict sparked reactions from the NAACP, which condemned it, while the father of the victim filed a lawsuit against Penny. The jury deliberated on a lesser charge of negligent homicide but could not reach a consensus and will resume deliberations on Monday. The case has garnered significant attention, highlighting issues of self-defense and the use of force.

name: Nikki Giovanni
summary: Celebrated poet and literary icon Nikki Giovanni has passed away at the age of 81. Throughout her illustrious career, Giovanni's poetry and activism resonated deeply with the Black community, earning her the moniker "The Princess of Black Poetry." As a professor at Virginia Tech, she inspired and nurtured countless students. Her work, characterized by its raw emotion, rhythmic language, and unapologetic exploration of Black identity, has been widely acclaimed for its truth-telling and resilience. Giovanni's legacy as a poet and activist will continue to profoundly impact literature, culture, and society for generations to come.
